Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack so that it is about 8-inches from flame
and preheat broiler to high. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}.
Quarter @heirloom grape tomatoes{4%oz}. Cut @lime{1} into wedges. Thinly slice
@scallions{2}. Trim root end from @shredded red cabbage{4%oz}, then slice leaves
into thin shreds.

In a #small bowl{}, stir together @sour cream{6%tbsp}, @Southwest spice blend{1%tsp}, and
a squeeze or two of lime. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a large, #ovenproof pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add onion and cook, tossing occasionally, until softened,
~{4-5%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Add @taco spice blend{2%tbsp} and
@tomato paste{1/4%cup} (we sent more) to pan. Stir until fragrant and
well combined, about ~{1%minute}.

Add @ground beef{20%oz} to pan, breaking up meat into pieces. Cook, tossing
occasionally, until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with plenty of salt and
pepper. Stir in @water{2%tbsp}, then sprinkle @cheddar cheese{1%cup} over top.
Transfer pan to broiler and broil until cheese is melted and bubbling, about
~{3%minutes}. Sprinkle with scallions.

While everything's broiling, wrap @flour tortillas{12} in a moistened
#paper towel{}. Microwave on high until warm and soft, about ~{30%seconds}.

Arrange lettuce, tomatoes, lime wedges, and crema into #bowls{} or #plates{}
for serving. Fill tortillas with beef mixture and divide between plates. Let
everyone add the toppings as they like and dig in!

